race.comment: WINE SNOB (5) should find this easier than his debut second at Balaklava three weeks ago. Draws to enjoy a lovely run and looks a strong follow-up chance. GOODLOOKIN' GURU (9) debuts as a well-bred Omaha Beach filly out of Glory Guru, a family with black-type depth. Has worked well in the lead-up and maps for a soft run from the draw. Can make an immediate impact. EVEN IN AMERICA (10) trialled well before her Morphettville return but didn't go on with it. Better for the outing and drawn far kinder under a light weight again. Worth another look. SIR MONICA (3) improved sharply last start when a close third at Bordertown. Rock-hard fit now and right in the mix. ARAMOSO (11) continues to chase that maiden win but has ratings scattered through his form that measure up. Didn't fire fresh, but that race has already produced three subsequent winners. Don't dismiss.
